reviews.text: A great station for regular commuters. Always a small stool for snacks and drinks. Very small ticket office/seating area, but lots of parking at the back (Now full usually) for regular users. A relative uses this station every work day. Great help.
Small train station with just two platforms. One for services north towards London and one southbound for services towards Hastings. The ticket office and is within what looks like an old church.
Lovely station with lots of parking space
I love this Station,long may it continue the way it is,it's great to have the option of a ticket office,too! The Taxi firm that operate from outside could be a little less surly,tho!
I like to walk, so I am not worried about the parking, which is two small. It kind of looks like a church. Nice little station.
